CC Sabathia will start for the  New
York Yankees  against  Justin Verlander  of the Detroit Tigers in
Game 3 of their Major League Baseball first-round playoff series
tomorrow.  The pitchers began the opening game of the American League
Division Series, which was rained off after 1 1/2 innings Sept.
30. New York won 9-3 after play resumed yesterday, with rookie
Ivan Nova taking over from Sabathia and Doug Fister going for
the Tigers.  Max Scherzer will start for Detroit and Freddy Garcia will
open for the Yankees in Game 2 today at Yankee Stadium in New
York.  New Yorkâ€™s A.J. Burnett will go againstRick Porcello in
